Dear Harry

This is great.
Many thanks indeed.

In 1977 (or so) Mac Lane gave a talk at Heidelberg
and mentioned
Max and Min, Lax and Lin,
the principle of Courant-Weyl
and other such issues.
From my recollections
he did not say he had ever taught a course on mechanics.

If I had obtained a copy of these notes in my mathematical youth,
that would have saved me a lot of trouble.

Best wishes

Johannes


